# Protocol-surface code owners (ADR-0042 companion hardening).
# With branch protection's "require review from Code Owners" on (enforce_admins off),
# a non-admin collaborator's PR touching these paths needs the maintainer's review.
# The maintainer (admin) and their agents are unaffected — agent self-merge stays intact.
# Mapping is by file path, deliberately one notch coarser than the L1/L2 semantic boundary.

/AGENTS.md          @real-stanyan
/CLAUDE.md          @real-stanyan
/CONTEXT.md         @real-stanyan
/docs/gearbox-adr/  @real-stanyan
/.github/           @real-stanyan
/scripts/           @real-stanyan
/.gearbox-version   @real-stanyan

# Publish surface (#124): these ship in the npm package (`files`) or execute at publish
# time — an unreviewed change here reaches every downstream on the maintainer's next
# `npm publish` (bin/ is the npx dispatcher; package.json carries the bin mapping and
# npm lifecycle scripts, i.e. code execution).
/bin/               @real-stanyan
/package.json       @real-stanyan
